				\begin{document}$$ \mathrm{T}\mathrm{G}\mathrm{F}-\upbeta $$\end{document}TGF-β, MAPK, STAT, PI3K, RAS and Cell Cycle/Apoptosis regulate “cell survival”; NOTCH, HH, APC, Chromatin modification and Transcriptional regulation regulate “cell fate”; while the DNA damage control signaling pathway regulates “genome maintenance”. We have separately analyzed the protein profiles of the three cancer types using “GO” clustering tool [3, 4] and grouped the proteins according to their biological pathways. As selective growth advantage can occur only through the “target pathways”, we have considered only the proteins included in the “target pathways” for our analysis.

