pr × p and N
cr × p, respectively. Now, a matrix E is constructed by merging the rows of the two profiles, i.e., E is of order (N
pr + N
cr) × p. Then, the rows of E are randomly permuted and the first N
pr patients are considered as one group and the remaining N
cr patients as another group. For the i
th permutation, the connectivity scores s
pp 'pr,i and s
pp 'cr,i between the proteins p and p ' are then computed using the expression profiles of the permuted data. Thus, the i
